.TH SLOF "5"

.SH NAME
.B slof
- Simple Line Oriented Format

.SH DESCRIPTION
Slof is a simple line oriented format for when you need an array of entries.

.SH SYNTAX
1. Any line that begins with a semicolon (';') is a comment.

2. To interpret a semicolon at the beginning of a line literally, it must be preceeded with a backslash.

3. Entire line is treated as an entry, and it's up to the program to decide what to do with the whitespace.
